        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 172,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "36bd7375ee334ca30404dac02062c504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "off-guard",
            "aonid": 58,
            "game-obj": "Conditions",
            "name": "off-guard",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Backstabber",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "When you hit an off-guard creature, this weapon deals 1 precision damage in addition to its normal damage. The precision damage increases to 2 if the weapon is a _+3 weapon_.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 178,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "db3dcba30733bab63da3438275614311",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Fatal",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The fatal trait includes a die size. On a critical hit, the weapon\u2019s damage die increases to that die size instead of the normal die size, and the weapon adds one additional damage die of the listed size.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "d10"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 224,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e803bedbfb9ec7c760a341f41b6807de",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "kobold",
            "aonid": 80,
            "game-obj": "Ancestries",
            "name": "kobold",
            "type": "link"
          },
          {
            "alt": "darkvision",
            "aonid": 2410,
            "game-obj": "Rules",
            "name": "darkvision",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Kobold",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 317",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 317",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core 2",
            "page": 317,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A creature with this trait is a member of the kobold ancestry, reptilian humanoids who are usually Small and typically have darkvision. An ability with this trait can be used or selected only by kobolds.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 271,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "34c8c3292092e7f05eaa086e75d06c7c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Interact",
            "aonid": 2297,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Interact",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Modular",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core 2",
            "page": 274,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The weapon has multiple configurations that you can switch between using an Interact action. Typically, switching between configurations of a modular weapon allows it to deal different types of damage (listed in the trait, such as \u201cmodular B, P, or S\u201d), though it's possible for a modular weapon's description to list more complicated configurations.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "(B, P, or S)"
      }
    ],
